UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1454
1 A RESOLUTION adjourning the Senate in honor and loving memory of Brian Jay
2 Hatt.
3 WHEREAS, Brian Jay Hatt was an esteemed resident of Raywick, Kentucky; and
4 WHEREAS, Brian Jay Hatt was the loving and beloved husband of Tonya Hatt; and
5 WHEREAS, Brian Jay Hatt was the loving and beloved father of Austin (Katie)
6 Hinshaw, Autumn Hatt, and Alayna Willson, and the loving and beloved grandfather of
7 Evelyn Willson and Jaycee Hinshaw; and
8 WHEREAS, Brian Jay Hatt answered the call to service to his country and was a
9 proud member of the United States Army; and
10 WHEREAS, Brian Jay Hatt also answered the call for service to his community,
11 serving with honor and distinction as a lieutenant with the Raywick Fire Department; and
12 WHEREAS, Brian Jay Hatt was universally known for his quick wit, being a man
13 of conscious action by helping those in need, and for his compassion to all; and
14 WHEREAS, Brian Jay Hatt passed from this life on August 25, 2025, when while
15 on route to assist a fellow fire department on a fire call, the tanker truck he was driving
16 was involved in a serious accident;
17 NOW, THEREFORE,
18 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
19 Kentucky:
20 Section 1. The Senate expresses its most profound sympathy upon the passing
21 of Brian Jay Hatt and extends heartfelt condolences to his family, friends, and
22 community.
23 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor and loving
24 memory of Brian Jay Hatt.
25 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
26 Resolution to Senator Jimmy Higdon for delivery to the family.
